The paper deals with the complexity of approximating partition functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. The use of combinatorial arguments suggests that the paper may fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of partition functions also involves information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category. The paper also discusses connections to quantum computation, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
